# NAS OS is Turnkey Linux FileServer

## Windows XP does not support GPT-formatted disks nor 2-terabyte plus partitions (although they do support NTFS filesystems)
# one of my disks is 5-terabytes, so I had to create a VM that uses turnkey Linux file server to host a samba connection
# this file server resides on an isolated LAN, that which only the Windows XP VM connects to.
# I am sure some people will argue against file servers for playing games, but this was the best solution for a seamless VFIO setup on my host.

